<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Grandview</ENAMEX> moves ahead withnew signals
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">GRANDVIEW</ENAMEX> - Grandview Public Works Director Cus Arteaga reported to city council <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Monday</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">night</TIMEX>, that work is currently being done on the design phase of the signalization projects at both the intersection of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Wine Country Road</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Elm Street</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Wine Country</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Grandridge</ENAMEX> roads.
The project will include some changes to the intersection of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Grandridge</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Wine Country</ENAMEX> roads. The corner of the intersection where Lucky Seven is located will be widened to create a larger turning radius.
According to the report given to council, the signals at both intersections will likely be installed later <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">this fall</TIMEX>.
